main event: Multiple observers reported sightings of unidentified flying objects in Moose Lake, Minnesota over various dates in August 1967.
interesting points: Approximately 20 persons watched a star-like object for over thirty minutes, The object changed brightness and tilted slightly, One observer later reported a similar sighting the following night, An observer described a round object with pulsating yellowish-orange light hovering at 1,000 feet altitude, Another sighting involved a large metallic object hovering silently over the lake.
sighted object: various unidentified flying objects, including a star-like object and a large metallic hovering object
witness description: Residents of Moose Lake, including Mr. and Mrs. John Strom.
